# AiDE Project Intelligence — Playwright React Perf E2E

## Critical Workflow
1. Developer records flow with `npm run codegen` (opens Chrome at BASE_URL)
2. Paste each generated action into a `measureRender()` wrapper in `tests/e2e.spec.ts`
3. Run `npm test` — performance report auto-prints to console
4. Run `npm run report` — opens HTML report with attached JSON

## Key Patterns
- NEVER write selectors manually — always use `playwright codegen`
- ALWAYS wrap user interactions in `measureRender()` from `tests/helpers/perfHelper.ts`
- Call `injectPerformanceObserver(page)` BEFORE `page.goto()` in every test
- Collect `getNavigationTiming(page)` AFTER `page.goto()` resolves
- Accumulate `RenderTiming[]` array, call `buildReport()` + `printReport()` at end of test
- Attach JSON report using `test.info().attach()`

## Environment
- OS: Windows 11, PowerShell
- Node: v26.2.0
- Use `npx playwright` (not global playwright)
- Set BASE_URL via `$env:BASE_URL = "http://localhost:PORT"` in PowerShell

## Performance Thresholds
- Slow action: >300ms (flagged in report summary)
- Average render assertion: <1000ms (fails test if exceeded)
- Both are configurable — see progress.md for locations

## File Roles
- `tests/e2e.spec.ts` — paste codegen output here (inside measureRender blocks)
- `tests/helpers/perfHelper.ts` — DO NOT modify unless adding new metric types
- `playwright.config.ts` — change BASE_URL, timeout, headless mode here
- `scripts/codegen.ps1` — use for guided codegen with instructions

## Common Mistakes to Avoid
- Do NOT use `workers > 1` — breaks rendering time accuracy
- Do NOT set `headless: true` — rendering skips paint phases in headless
- Do NOT use `'commit'` in `waitForLoadState()` — not supported by Playwright
- Do NOT forget `await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle')` before `getNavigationTiming()`

## npm init playwright Behavior
- `npm init playwright@latest` interactive wizard got stuck on this machine
- Always create `package.json`, `playwright.config.ts`, test files manually instead
- Run `npm install` and `npx playwright install chromium` separately
